WEBVTT

00:06.006 --> 00:07.590
[radio static crackling]

00:07.674 --> 00:10.260
[reporter] People are on edge
as rumors swirl about impending attack

00:10.343 --> 00:14.764
as we approach the 40th anniversary
of George Hutchence, also known as Skyfox,

00:14.848 --> 00:16.433
leaving the Union.

00:16.516 --> 00:18.768
[Jack] Are you hearing this, mate?

00:18.852 --> 00:21.104
They're talking about your father
on the radio.

00:21.604 --> 00:24.733
Do you mind telling us why
we're not backing you up on this heist?

00:26.317 --> 00:28.737
If you're pulling a Phil Collins, I swear…

00:28.820 --> 00:29.654
Phil Collins?

00:29.738 --> 00:32.032
Going solo.
Ditching us like he left Genesis.

00:32.115 --> 00:34.451
-[Hutch] I'm not leaving anybody.
-Who's Genesis?

00:34.534 --> 00:35.577
[Hutch] Here we go.

00:36.244 --> 00:37.620
Uh… [scoffs]

00:38.413 --> 00:41.916
What was it like
when Beyoncé left Destiny's Child?

00:42.000 --> 00:44.127
Good for Beyoncé,
not so much for the others.

00:44.711 --> 00:46.296
He's pulling a Beyoncé.

00:46.379 --> 00:50.008
Actually, I prefer the classics,
Brunettes, Shirelles.

00:50.884 --> 00:54.012
This is how it starts.
You do one gig alone. It goes well--

00:54.095 --> 00:55.805
Then you realize
you don't need us anymore.

00:55.889 --> 00:58.975
Look, we haven't had a big score lately,
but it's just a slump.

00:59.059 --> 01:00.852
And we're following your rules,

01:00.935 --> 01:03.396
never kill, all that stuff.

01:03.480 --> 01:05.899
Look, I would never think
about leaving you.

01:05.982 --> 01:07.150
How can we be sure, mate?

01:07.233 --> 01:10.570
Because we have been friends
since we were kids. We're family.

01:10.653 --> 01:13.740
Hey, if this is a job for the Big Man,
all our asses are on the line.

01:13.823 --> 01:16.201
[Hutch] Guys, the Big Man wants
the Quantum Modular,

01:16.284 --> 01:20.747
and he wants no clues left behind,
nothing that can get traced back to him,

01:20.830 --> 01:22.415
which is why I'm going alone.

01:22.916 --> 01:25.794
And with this,
no one will ever know I was there.

01:28.922 --> 01:30.590
[electronic beeping]

01:38.098 --> 01:39.891
[indistinct shouting]

01:41.810 --> 01:43.394
[robber 1] When do the buyers arrive?

01:43.478 --> 01:45.396
[robber 2] You know how they are. [grunts]

01:45.480 --> 01:48.650
[robber 1] Yeah,
they're always late. [grunts]

01:48.733 --> 01:51.402
[robber 2] Speaking of late,
when do you think that we're gonna get…

01:54.823 --> 01:56.658
[robbers chattering indistinctly]

01:56.741 --> 01:57.826
Back of the van.

02:00.411 --> 02:02.330
[robber 2] You got
a billion to burn, my brother.

02:05.542 --> 02:06.709
[gun cocking]

02:07.502 --> 02:11.297
We've got an intruder in the van.
Hey, drop whatever the hell that is.

02:11.381 --> 02:12.382
Safe place.

02:13.883 --> 02:14.843
[shouts]

02:15.677 --> 02:16.511
[gasps]

02:16.594 --> 02:18.388
-[pants]
-[whooshing]

02:22.433 --> 02:23.935
-[robber 2] Utopian!
-[robber 3] Shit!

02:26.062 --> 02:27.063
Aw, hell!

02:27.147 --> 02:29.107
-[man 1] Utopian!
-[man 2] Check him out!

02:29.190 --> 02:30.775
[robber 2] Die, goddamn it!

02:31.442 --> 02:33.778
Unleash! Come on! Let's go!

02:33.862 --> 02:34.779
Back of the van.

02:47.792 --> 02:48.918
Shit!

02:49.419 --> 02:50.420
Loft!

02:55.925 --> 02:57.051
[sighs]

03:00.763 --> 03:01.764
[sighs]

03:07.478 --> 03:09.272
[dramatic music playing]

03:58.529 --> 04:02.700
["Painting the Clouds With Sunshine"
by Jean Goldkette & His Orchestra playing]

04:02.784 --> 04:04.702
♪ When I pretend I'm gay ♪

04:04.786 --> 04:07.038
-♪ I never feel that way ♪
-[sighs]

04:07.121 --> 04:09.332
-♪ I'm only painting ♪
-[chuckles, grunts]

04:09.415 --> 04:12.210
♪ The clouds with sunshine ♪

04:12.293 --> 04:14.545
♪ When I hold back a tear ♪

04:14.629 --> 04:17.173
-♪ To make a smile appear ♪
-[inhales]

04:17.257 --> 04:19.884
-♪ I'm only painting the clouds ♪
-[humming]

04:19.968 --> 04:21.469
♪ With sunshine ♪

04:22.387 --> 04:24.806
♪ Painting the blues beautiful hues ♪

04:24.889 --> 04:27.225
♪ Colored with gold and old rose ♪

04:27.308 --> 04:31.938
♪ Playing the clown
Trying to drown all of my woes ♪

04:32.021 --> 04:34.399
♪ Though things may not look bright ♪

04:34.482 --> 04:36.859
♪ They all turn out all right ♪

04:36.943 --> 04:39.779
-♪ If I keep painting the clouds ♪
-[whistling]

04:39.862 --> 04:42.031
♪ With sunshine ♪

04:45.785 --> 04:48.037
Good morning, sir. I trust you slept well?

04:48.121 --> 04:50.873
Oh, like a drunk baby in his mama's arms.

04:50.957 --> 04:53.209
-The way God intended, sir.
-[chuckles]

04:54.294 --> 04:56.838
Are you being cheeky, Cuthbert?
Was that cheek?

04:56.921 --> 04:59.340
All tongue and lips, I assure you, sir.

04:59.424 --> 05:02.677
-Did Wingate send over the papers?
-[Cuthbert] In your study, sir.

05:02.760 --> 05:05.805
-[indistinct chattering]
-Ah. Thank you.

05:06.889 --> 05:10.393
The chef has prepared 99 eggs,

05:10.476 --> 05:14.105
boiled to varying degrees,
exactly as you like them.

05:14.188 --> 05:16.149
Which will it be today, sir?

05:16.649 --> 05:17.483
Hmm.

05:18.401 --> 05:19.944
Let's go with a number 72.

05:20.528 --> 05:22.238
[Cuthbert] Excellent choice, sir.

05:26.409 --> 05:27.493
[humming]

05:27.577 --> 05:28.411
[Walter] George!

05:29.037 --> 05:31.205
-I'm sorry, sir. They just--
-No. It's all right.

05:31.289 --> 05:33.791
Come in. I was just sitting for breakfast.
Have an egg.

05:33.875 --> 05:37.086
Cuthbert, number, uh, 82
for the lady, please.

05:37.170 --> 05:42.050
And for the gentleman,
a number 12, soft-boiled.

05:42.759 --> 05:44.761
-We've already eaten, thank you.
-All right.

05:44.844 --> 05:45.845
Where have you been?

05:45.928 --> 05:48.973
Oh, here, there,
everywhere the mood takes me. [chuckles]

05:49.057 --> 05:50.516
Except where you're needed.

05:51.601 --> 05:53.936
Is something
chewing on your shorts, Walter?

05:54.020 --> 05:57.315
Let's be out with it, hmm?
Insinuation's bad for the digestion.

05:58.733 --> 05:59.734
[Jane] It's Sheldon.

06:02.195 --> 06:03.196
He's…

06:03.780 --> 06:04.614
[sighs]

06:06.032 --> 06:07.283
He's not well.

06:10.495 --> 06:11.412
Bushwa.

06:12.497 --> 06:14.665
He snapped out
of whatever that was at the funeral.

06:14.749 --> 06:18.628
-Medical boys gave him a clean bill.
-It's not physical, George. It's…

06:19.462 --> 06:21.422
At least, they don't think it is.

06:22.382 --> 06:25.218
He, um… he's not eating.

06:26.886 --> 06:28.638
He hasn't slept in days.

06:28.721 --> 06:29.639
[Jane] And he's…

06:32.558 --> 06:35.019
Well, he's just not himself, that's all.

06:36.437 --> 06:37.271
Huh.

06:37.980 --> 06:39.941
Yeah. It's been tough on all of us.

06:41.526 --> 06:43.236
Not everyone, it looks like.

06:43.694 --> 06:44.737
Hmm.

06:45.238 --> 06:47.407
Will you please visit, George?

06:48.157 --> 06:50.993
-Seeing you will help. I know it will.
-Yes. Yes, of course.

06:51.077 --> 06:53.663
I'll stop by on the way
to the benefit tonight.

06:54.163 --> 06:55.665
-[Jane] Thank you.
-Oh! Okay. All right.

06:55.748 --> 06:58.376
Don't get all soggy on me.
Sheldon will be just fine.

06:59.252 --> 07:00.503
How would you know?

07:01.170 --> 07:03.881
Because it is all
about the attitude, chum.

07:03.965 --> 07:07.343
Chin up, eyes forward.
Paint the clouds with sunshine.

07:09.220 --> 07:10.847
[Jack] Jesus Christ!

07:11.431 --> 07:15.059
Everything's gonna be all right.
Just relax. Let me handle it.

07:15.143 --> 07:16.727
Relax? Yeah, right, mate.

07:17.562 --> 07:20.690
There's no way the Big Man
doesn't slap the shit out of us for this.

07:20.773 --> 07:21.983
Popsicle is right.

07:22.567 --> 07:24.527
You should've let us help.
Now we gotta get out of here.

07:24.610 --> 07:27.447
-He can get to anyone, anyplace, anytime.
-[Jack] Mm-hmm.

07:27.530 --> 07:30.116
If he doesn't squeeze our nuts off,
the Union will.

07:30.199 --> 07:32.785
Do you wanna end up
in the Supermax with Blackstar?

07:32.869 --> 07:34.996
Jack, shut up and listen.

07:35.496 --> 07:37.498
It's on me. I got it.

07:37.582 --> 07:39.333
-You hope.
-I know.

07:40.460 --> 07:41.461
Trust me.

07:43.796 --> 07:47.008
I still say we hit the road.
There's plenty of room in the van.

07:47.508 --> 07:48.759
-[phone chimes]
-Hmm.

07:49.969 --> 07:53.556
-[Jacinda] Is it him?
-No. It's personal.

07:55.057 --> 07:58.436
Keep your head screwed on.
Don't do anything stupid.

08:00.354 --> 08:01.189
[Jacinda] Hmm.

08:02.064 --> 08:06.194
-[man 1 over phone] You're late.
-I know. There was a complication.

08:06.277 --> 08:09.489
-[man 1] There is another buyer.
-I'm your buyer.

08:09.989 --> 08:12.366
[man 1] Then where is my money?

08:12.450 --> 08:14.785
We had a deal, you goddamn Nazi.

08:14.869 --> 08:17.955
[man 1] All are equal in my eyes,
if they can pay.

08:18.039 --> 08:19.123
[sighs]

08:19.999 --> 08:23.419
I'll get you your money.
Just give me till the end of the week.

08:23.503 --> 08:24.462
[man 1] Two days.

08:25.213 --> 08:26.631
That Nazi comment,

08:27.840 --> 08:31.636
it will regrettably cost you
an extra ten percent.

08:31.719 --> 08:32.553
[line hangs up]

08:34.138 --> 08:35.181
Shit.

08:36.140 --> 08:37.141
[man 2] Rough night?

08:37.934 --> 08:39.185
About to get rougher.

08:39.977 --> 08:41.020
Linus.

08:41.896 --> 08:43.022
Lucy.

08:43.105 --> 08:45.024
It's Kevin, you freaking mutt!

08:45.107 --> 08:48.402
He knows who you are, and he knows
why we're here, don't you, Hutch?

08:49.320 --> 08:54.742
Yeah. Look… something's just come up.
Could we maybe do this some other time?

08:54.825 --> 08:56.285
[Kevin] Some other time?

09:04.877 --> 09:06.671
No time like the present, huh?

09:09.507 --> 09:10.341
To the Big Man.

09:16.806 --> 09:18.307
[Sheldon yelling indistinctly]

09:18.933 --> 09:20.685
Get out of my head! Stop it!

09:21.227 --> 09:22.144
Get away!

09:23.104 --> 09:26.190
No! No! There's no reason why!

09:29.485 --> 09:31.320
Let me figure it out myself!

09:33.155 --> 09:33.990
Shel?

09:34.073 --> 09:36.284
[Sheldon continues yelling indistinctly]

09:36.367 --> 09:39.328
It's me, George. I…
I got all dressed up for you. [chuckles]

09:39.412 --> 09:41.414
[Sheldon continues yelling indistinctly]

09:42.331 --> 09:43.165
[clears throat]

09:44.083 --> 09:45.042
[exhales deeply]

09:45.835 --> 09:47.378
Georgie.

09:49.880 --> 09:50.881
Come on.

09:51.841 --> 09:53.676
Come on.
Come on, come on, come on, come on.

09:55.595 --> 09:56.679
[exhales deeply]

09:57.972 --> 09:58.806
[grunts]

10:01.309 --> 10:03.728
[George] Uh, who… who were you talking to?

10:04.228 --> 10:05.646
Oh, uh…

10:05.730 --> 10:10.151
[splutters] Nobody.
I was… I was just thinking out loud.

10:10.818 --> 10:13.613
Now, that is a handsome man.

10:14.196 --> 10:16.616
[George] Uh, you know,
you gotta be careful with that.

10:16.699 --> 10:18.951
Folks will get
the wrong notion. [chuckles]

10:19.035 --> 10:19.869
Yeah.

10:20.328 --> 10:21.329
[chuckles]

10:21.871 --> 10:23.122
[Sheldon] Stop it.

10:25.041 --> 10:26.000
Stop what?

10:27.585 --> 10:29.962
[spits] Nothing. Nothing.

10:31.380 --> 10:33.090
Why are you here, George?

10:33.716 --> 10:35.760
Shel, they're worried about you.

10:38.054 --> 10:41.807
[sighs] Look, I can't talk anymore,
all right? I gotta get back to work.

10:47.772 --> 10:48.606
[exhales deeply]

10:55.071 --> 10:56.072
[sighs]

10:56.906 --> 10:58.532
I didn't know you draw.

10:58.616 --> 11:00.868
I don't. Well, I… [laughs]

11:00.951 --> 11:02.745
I didn't, and… and…

11:03.788 --> 11:04.747
[sighs]

11:08.167 --> 11:09.460
Look, Shel…

11:10.544 --> 11:13.339
I'm real sorry that I wasn't here before,
but I'm here now, buddy.

11:13.422 --> 11:15.549
-[Chester] Don't listen to him.
-[groans]

11:15.633 --> 11:20.221
He's just here for the spectacle,
because that's what they want.

11:20.304 --> 11:22.473
That's what they all want.

11:22.556 --> 11:23.432
Come on, pal.

11:23.516 --> 11:24.350
[grunts]

11:24.433 --> 11:27.603
They want to see you end up like this.

11:27.687 --> 11:30.314
-Get away from me!
-[exclaims] Sheldon!

11:30.398 --> 11:32.191
[Sheldon panting]

11:40.783 --> 11:43.369
-[gasping]
-[George] Okay. I got you. All right.

11:43.452 --> 11:46.664
-You're okay.
-George, I don't think I'm okay.

11:47.623 --> 11:50.876
I think maybe I'm not… okay.

11:50.960 --> 11:52.294
Okay. All right. Uh…

11:53.087 --> 11:56.215
Hey, why don't you, uh…
why don't you sit, huh? Have a seat.

11:56.298 --> 11:58.676
Go on. Go, go, go. Here, have a seat.

11:59.343 --> 12:00.469
[panting]

12:02.054 --> 12:02.888
Uh…

12:05.933 --> 12:07.184
[panting]

12:07.268 --> 12:09.562
Shel. Hey.

12:15.401 --> 12:17.695
Walt thinks I'm going around the bend…

12:19.071 --> 12:19.905
and Jane too.

12:19.989 --> 12:22.366
[George] Oh, come on, Shel.
You're grieving.

12:23.367 --> 12:24.744
You'll get past this.

12:25.870 --> 12:26.996
Have you?

12:29.206 --> 12:30.040
Have you?

12:31.292 --> 12:33.711
I've known you my whole life,

12:33.794 --> 12:36.172
and you've barely said two words
about your parents,

12:36.255 --> 12:37.715
about what… what happened to them.

12:37.798 --> 12:39.133
Well, life happened.

12:40.551 --> 12:41.510
And then…

12:44.263 --> 12:45.473
And then it stopped.

12:50.686 --> 12:52.772
Life happened, and then it stopped?

12:55.858 --> 12:56.776
That's it?

12:58.194 --> 13:00.154
[thunder rumbling]

13:01.697 --> 13:03.574
He did it right in front of me.

13:04.450 --> 13:06.660
Don't! No, Dad!

13:07.244 --> 13:08.621
[screaming]

13:11.123 --> 13:13.501
Why would he do that? Why would he do it?

13:15.336 --> 13:19.423
Why would he…
why would he do that right in front of me?

13:19.507 --> 13:20.424
I don't know.

13:20.508 --> 13:22.343
[Sheldon exhales sharply]

13:25.721 --> 13:26.972
At least you, uh…

13:29.141 --> 13:30.810
At least you got to see him.

13:35.314 --> 13:38.025
One day, good old Mum was flush as a rose,

13:39.276 --> 13:41.153
and then she, uh, caught a fever.

13:43.656 --> 13:45.991
And so scared
that she'd pass it along to me

13:46.075 --> 13:47.701
that she wouldn't even let me in the room.

13:52.164 --> 13:53.499
Not even at the end.

13:55.918 --> 13:56.794
[inhales sharply]

13:56.877 --> 13:59.296
And then Dad, he went the following year.

13:59.964 --> 14:01.215
Heart gave out.

14:04.218 --> 14:05.052
[sniffles]

14:05.970 --> 14:08.138
You know,
sometimes I look at you and Walt,

14:08.222 --> 14:13.686
and I wonder… what it would've been like

14:13.769 --> 14:17.106
if they had lived just a little longer,
you know, if I hadn't been alone?

14:18.190 --> 14:21.068
Well… [chuckles] I mean, there's Cuthbert,

14:21.151 --> 14:25.364
but, uh, he's hardly what I would call
a scintillating conversationalist.

14:26.782 --> 14:28.659
[breathing softly]

14:30.202 --> 14:31.871
[thunder rumbling]

14:55.060 --> 14:56.186
[thunder crashing]

15:01.400 --> 15:03.819
[ominous music playing]

15:31.555 --> 15:32.431
Hello.

15:33.098 --> 15:34.892
[Big Man grunting]

15:38.604 --> 15:40.105
[toilet flushing]

15:50.324 --> 15:52.409
[Big Man] Where is my Quantum Modular?

15:53.327 --> 15:54.870
[sighs]

15:59.124 --> 16:01.835
Well, I'm waiting.

16:05.130 --> 16:07.883
Hey, look, I know I screwed up,
but I promise you--

16:07.967 --> 16:09.718
[air blowing]

16:15.891 --> 16:16.976
[grunts]

16:19.645 --> 16:20.646
You were saying?

16:21.522 --> 16:23.190
[grunts]

16:24.358 --> 16:25.234
[chuckles]

16:25.317 --> 16:29.279
You are one hard son of a bitch
for a shit with no powers.

16:29.989 --> 16:30.823
I like that.

16:31.907 --> 16:33.784
But that crew of yours,

16:33.867 --> 16:37.246
maybe if I take them apart
a piece at a time,

16:38.580 --> 16:40.082
that'll soften you up.

16:41.375 --> 16:42.584
[chuckles wryly]

16:44.044 --> 16:48.924
And that right there
is why you're a stupid little shit.

16:49.008 --> 16:50.634
I thought we already agreed on that.

16:52.219 --> 16:53.679
Don't sass me, boy,

16:53.762 --> 16:57.349
or I'll take that little toy of yours
and jam it up your ass.

16:57.433 --> 16:59.518
How can I make this right?

17:03.731 --> 17:05.274
Kulakov Brothers

17:06.275 --> 17:09.111
are delivering a briefcase
to the Hun tomorrow night.

17:09.194 --> 17:12.948
Take it off their hands.
We'll call it a push.

17:13.032 --> 17:14.158
What's in the case?

17:15.325 --> 17:16.326
Your lives.

17:18.579 --> 17:19.830
We'll get it for you.

17:21.623 --> 17:22.708
And get a haircut.

17:23.333 --> 17:25.377
-[sighs]
-You look like an idiot.

17:26.712 --> 17:27.880
Thanks for the tip.

17:29.339 --> 17:30.257
Loft.

17:31.508 --> 17:32.968
[moaning]

17:33.052 --> 17:34.720
[electricity zapping]

17:34.803 --> 17:37.014
[hip-hop music playing]

17:37.097 --> 17:38.724
[moaning continues]

17:38.807 --> 17:41.185
[gasps, shouts in Portuguese]

17:41.769 --> 17:43.479
Shit! Would it kill you to use the door?

17:43.562 --> 17:46.190
Sorry. It's important.

17:46.273 --> 17:47.733
Yeah, so was this, asshole.

17:48.317 --> 17:49.610
The Big Man reached out.

17:51.695 --> 17:54.031
-What did he say?
-That I screwed up.

17:54.114 --> 17:56.617
We know you screwed up. Jesus! What else?

17:56.700 --> 17:59.495
[inhales deeply] He's got a job for us.

18:02.039 --> 18:04.875
We just have to take a briefcase
off the Kulakov Brothers.

18:05.751 --> 18:08.253
-The Russians?
-[shouting in Portuguese]

18:08.337 --> 18:10.297
You wanna tell the Big Man no, Jacinda?

18:11.090 --> 18:12.132
[sighs]

18:14.384 --> 18:15.552
[smacks lips] When?

18:18.305 --> 18:19.139
Tonight…

18:19.223 --> 18:20.390
-[scoffs]
-[groans]

18:20.474 --> 18:22.476
…before they deliver it to the Hun.

18:23.060 --> 18:25.104
Wow. It keeps getting better and better.

18:25.187 --> 18:26.772
-Mm-hmm.
-Is Jack in?

18:27.981 --> 18:28.816
Yeah.

18:29.566 --> 18:30.442
We need Jack.

18:30.526 --> 18:31.735
I'll talk to him.

18:31.819 --> 18:33.862
No, we need his van, Hutch.

18:33.946 --> 18:35.447
I will talk to him.

18:38.659 --> 18:40.536
No way he'd leave us hanging.

18:40.619 --> 18:41.912
Hell, no!

18:42.454 --> 18:45.916
-This is gonna make it right.
-This is gonna make us dead.

18:47.167 --> 18:49.545
The Kulakov Brothers,
they're freakin' animals!

18:49.628 --> 18:51.922
