I ever stay mad at you, Mary?

24:18.915 --> 24:20.125
-Margaret.
-Margaret.

24:21.960 --> 24:22.794
[clears throat]

24:23.295 --> 24:27.382
Uh, but, you know, maybe you ought to keep
your sister from playing with matches.

24:27.466 --> 24:31.094
-[laughs] We'll pay for the boat, I swear.
-Oh, family's still flush, are they?

24:31.178 --> 24:34.014
Well, Daddy had to sell the estate
in France, but we're getting by.

24:34.097 --> 24:36.933
Mmm. Well, what's one estate,
more or less?

24:37.017 --> 24:38.185
[laughs]

24:39.144 --> 24:42.439
Well, I'm just glad you've kept
your pretty little head above the waves.

24:42.522 --> 24:45.859
Well, I'm a strong swimmer.
You know, that helps when your boat sinks.

24:45.942 --> 24:47.527
[laughing] Oh, George!

24:48.403 --> 24:49.237
[Mary giggles]

24:49.321 --> 24:51.781
[Margaret]
Oh, she's got that look in her eye.

24:52.282 --> 24:55.744
We'd better go over there before she
starts doing something dreadful.

24:55.827 --> 24:59.206
Okay. You start smoothing her feathers.
I'll join you in a minute.

25:00.790 --> 25:01.708
[chuckles]

25:07.881 --> 25:08.798
All right.

25:22.312 --> 25:24.648
[ominous music playing]

25:26.024 --> 25:26.942
[George gasps]

25:35.075 --> 25:38.411
Hey, Georgie, give me something
for the society page, will ya?

25:39.663 --> 25:40.747
[exhales]

25:57.264 --> 25:59.599
-[Sheldon yelling indistinctly]
-[sighs]

26:06.147 --> 26:07.148
[Sheldon] Come in!

26:10.527 --> 26:11.778
[Jane] Stop! No!

26:11.861 --> 26:14.864
[laughs] George!
We were just talking about you.

26:14.948 --> 26:15.782
[laughs]

26:15.865 --> 26:19.202
Oh. If this is what happens
to a fella with you on his lap, hop on.

26:19.286 --> 26:20.287
-[Jane] Mmm.
-[chuckles]

26:20.370 --> 26:21.538
Easy there, pal.

26:21.621 --> 26:23.707
That's the future Mrs. Sampson
you're making eyes at.

26:23.790 --> 26:25.458
Hey, can you blame me?

26:25.542 --> 26:28.169
Hey, whatever tonic you juiced him with,
you ought to bottle that.

26:28.253 --> 26:29.671
I mean, he could use a shave but…

26:29.754 --> 26:31.381
-[chuckles]
-I had nothing to do with it.

26:31.464 --> 26:33.592
Oh, don't tell me Walt sat on his lap too?

26:33.675 --> 26:37.220
-[Jane chuckles]
-Mm. "Life happened, and then it stopped."

26:37.304 --> 26:39.306
Your words. Simple as that.

26:39.389 --> 26:41.391
No… no great mystery.

26:41.474 --> 26:43.810
-No secret messages from beyond the grave.
-Sheldon…

26:43.893 --> 26:47.230
I just closed my eyes and kept repeating
over and over and over what you said,

26:47.314 --> 26:49.899
"Life happened, and then it stopped."

26:50.734 --> 26:53.945
And when I opened my eyes back up,
it's like I didn't see…

26:56.698 --> 26:58.325
I didn't see the past anymore.

26:58.950 --> 27:00.827
I just saw the future. [chuckles]

27:02.704 --> 27:03.538
Hmm.

27:04.414 --> 27:06.333
Chin up, eyes forward.

27:06.833 --> 27:07.834
That's right.

27:09.336 --> 27:12.631
Well, the lap doesn't look big enough
for the both of us, so, uh, do me a favor.

27:12.714 --> 27:15.258
Wait till the door closes behind me.
I got delicate eyes.

27:15.342 --> 27:18.553
-[chuckles]
-Don't be silly! I'll make coffee.

27:20.180 --> 27:21.014
[whispers] Thank you.

27:24.184 --> 27:25.018
[chuckles]

27:25.810 --> 27:27.979
She whispers so loud,
you could hear it next door.

27:28.063 --> 27:29.731
-[George] My ear's ringing.
-Yeah.

27:30.774 --> 27:33.360
But she is right… to thank you.

27:34.861 --> 27:37.656
If you hadn't dropped by,
who knows? I might've…

27:38.657 --> 27:41.743
I don't know. I might've found
my own roof to jump off of.

27:43.703 --> 27:44.996
Don't ever say that.

27:47.874 --> 27:49.542
I actually thought about it.

27:54.756 --> 27:56.716
Don't tell Jane or Walt.

27:58.009 --> 27:59.928
God, if… if he knew,

28:00.011 --> 28:02.681
he'd have me locked up
before you could even take your tie off.

28:02.764 --> 28:04.391
I'm not gonna tell anybody.

28:08.186 --> 28:09.437
What do you got there?

28:11.606 --> 28:12.816
Nothing. Uh…

28:13.858 --> 28:16.528
I just borrowed a few of your drawings.

28:17.612 --> 28:18.905
[chuckling]

28:18.988 --> 28:21.241
Throw 'em in the fire
with the rest of it, would you?

28:21.825 --> 28:22.659
You burned 'em?

28:22.742 --> 28:25.620
[laughs] They were nothing.
They were just crazy doodles.

28:29.249 --> 28:30.500
What if they weren't?

28:32.669 --> 28:34.170
Take a look at this, huh?

28:35.630 --> 28:40.802
So, uh, there was something
about these shapes,

28:40.885 --> 28:44.180
something that, uh… something
I… I couldn't stop thinking about.

28:44.264 --> 28:48.935
You know, it was like a… like a puzzle
that needed to be solved.

28:49.018 --> 28:50.186
Is that a windmill?

28:51.604 --> 28:55.734
Maybe you saw it when you were a kid.
Someplace your father took you?

28:58.194 --> 28:59.946
We need to throw these in the fire.

29:00.029 --> 29:02.574
No, no, no, no.
It… it's not a message, Shel.

29:02.657 --> 29:04.951
It's a… it's a memory,

29:05.034 --> 29:07.203
a fragment, something you forgot, but…

29:07.287 --> 29:09.706
No. I've never seen this before.

29:09.789 --> 29:10.749
[George] Ah, Shel…

29:11.249 --> 29:14.252
Oh, it's too late for that, kid.

29:14.335 --> 29:15.754
[panting]

29:15.837 --> 29:18.047
[ominous music playing]

29:18.131 --> 29:18.965
Sheldon?

29:20.550 --> 29:22.761
[groaning]

29:23.219 --> 29:24.220
Get out!

29:25.180 --> 29:26.097
[grunts]

29:27.891 --> 29:29.684
[grunting]

29:32.395 --> 29:34.564
-[gasps]
-[metal creaking]

29:37.066 --> 29:38.902
[whooshing]

29:46.367 --> 29:48.328
[dog barking]

29:55.001 --> 29:56.753
[gasps]

29:56.836 --> 30:00.340
[George] Shel, don't try to move.
Don't try to move. I'm gonna ring the doc.

30:04.677 --> 30:06.012
Shel, just… just stay right there.

30:06.095 --> 30:09.098
I have to go.
[panting] I have to find this.

30:09.182 --> 30:10.391
-[line rings]
-[woman] Operator.

30:10.475 --> 30:12.644
Yes. Uh, hello, operator. Uh, I need--

30:12.727 --> 30:13.812
Sheldon?

30:13.895 --> 30:15.855
-[woman] Hello?
-I… I'm sorry. Just one…

30:16.397 --> 30:17.774
[woman] How can I help you?

30:17.857 --> 30:19.609
[George] Sheldon! [echoing]

30:21.569 --> 30:23.029
What were you thinking?

30:23.655 --> 30:26.366
Telling him you saw something
in those crazy scribbles.

30:26.449 --> 30:27.909
Well, I told him the truth.

30:27.992 --> 30:30.745
Since when did the great George Hutchence
ever care about the truth?

30:30.829 --> 30:33.206
-The hell does that mean?
-[Walter] Well, look at you.

30:33.289 --> 30:37.502
All dressed up as though your life
is nothing but flowers and sunshine.

30:39.671 --> 30:41.005
I heard about Wingate.

30:41.798 --> 30:43.132
You're broke.

30:43.216 --> 30:44.551
This isn't about me.

30:44.634 --> 30:47.011
[Walter scoffs]
It's always about you, George.

30:47.971 --> 30:50.098
You're the center of the goddamn universe.

30:50.807 --> 30:51.975
Well, not anymore.

30:52.475 --> 30:54.686
I know what I saw, Walt. Sheldon--

30:54.769 --> 30:56.604
Sheldon's lost his mind!

30:57.188 --> 30:59.232
[footsteps approaching]

31:00.567 --> 31:01.401
[gasps]

31:02.610 --> 31:03.444
[sighs]

31:03.528 --> 31:06.364
Uh, Jane, I'm… I am so sorry.

31:08.616 --> 31:09.492
[Jane] For what?

31:10.159 --> 31:12.412
It's true, isn't it?

31:18.668 --> 31:19.669
Did you find him?

31:22.589 --> 31:23.673
No.

31:24.799 --> 31:28.595
-I'll alert the authorities. Maybe--
-The police? Is that really necessary?

31:28.678 --> 31:32.640
Yes, George. You threw gas on the fire
and burned the house down.

31:32.724 --> 31:35.059
Now everyone's gonna know that Sheldon's--

31:35.643 --> 31:36.686
[Jane sighs]

31:36.769 --> 31:38.563
[weeping]

31:40.815 --> 31:41.983
That he's not well.

31:43.401 --> 31:44.277
Walt?

31:44.360 --> 31:45.653
You know the way out.

31:51.117 --> 31:52.035
[sighs]

31:53.202 --> 31:57.790
Janey, I would never do anything
to hurt Sheldon. He's my best friend.

31:57.874 --> 31:59.000
But he isn't here.

32:00.501 --> 32:01.711
[sighs]

32:02.837 --> 32:03.713
Is he?

32:07.091 --> 32:08.134
[sighs]

32:18.311 --> 32:19.938
[pool balls rattling]

32:20.021 --> 32:22.231
[pop music playing in background]

32:23.483 --> 32:24.943
[sighs]

32:36.120 --> 32:36.996
[Linus] Hutch.

32:38.831 --> 32:40.708
Big Man's been waiting for you.

32:42.418 --> 32:47.298
It has been a long day, boys.
Any chance we can do this in the morning?

32:47.382 --> 32:49.634
You're all out of chances,
you little shit.

32:50.426 --> 32:52.512
-Where's the case?
-We had it.

32:53.721 --> 32:56.933
We took it off the Kulakov Brothers,
just like we were told.

32:57.016 --> 32:58.559
Then our van hit this girl.

32:58.643 --> 33:00.395
The hell do we care?

33:00.478 --> 33:03.773
Because it wasn't just any girl.
It was Chloe Sampson.

33:05.149 --> 33:06.818
-You're shitting me.
-[chuckles]

33:06.901 --> 33:10.488
The Utopian's daughter? This guy, Linus…

33:10.571 --> 33:11.948
So she took the case?

33:12.031 --> 33:14.826
Just what was left inside, one bag.

33:14.909 --> 33:16.953
[Linus] Well, get it back.
Maybe he'll go easy on you.

33:17.036 --> 33:20.999
-It's gone.
-So use your magic jerk rod and go get it.

33:21.082 --> 33:24.127
Already tried. It's gone. Live with it.

33:24.210 --> 33:25.920
[Kevin] Yeah, we can live with it,

33:27.088 --> 33:30.800
but you and your shithead friends won't.

33:33.845 --> 33:36.639
Really wish
you hadn't said that about my friends.

33:39.517 --> 33:40.560
[glass shatters]

33:42.020 --> 33:44.522
Now who's got your little toy, asshole?

33:45.106 --> 33:46.024
You do, Lucy.

33:47.233 --> 33:48.943
Shark-infested waters.

33:53.573 --> 33:55.199
The hell you just do?

33:55.283 --> 33:57.744
Thought the description
was pretty freakin' clear.

33:58.411 --> 33:59.620
Home.

34:02.999 --> 34:04.208
You see… [chuckles]

34:04.792 --> 34:05.918
…common misconception.

34:07.170 --> 34:09.088
It doesn't matter who's holding this.

34:11.591 --> 34:13.509
It only listens to me.

34:15.053 --> 34:16.721
We were just following
the Big Man's orders.

34:16.804 --> 34:17.972
You know that, right?

34:19.599 --> 34:20.433
Yeah.

34:22.560 --> 34:24.520
So what would you do in this situation

34:25.271 --> 34:27.231
if you were the one calling the shots?

34:30.443 --> 34:31.319
Bygones.

34:33.988 --> 34:34.989
Big Man's heart.

34:49.212 --> 34:50.213
Home.

34:57.428 --> 34:59.388
I broke a promise tonight, Linus,

35:00.389 --> 35:03.518
when I did that to Lucy, Big Man.

35:03.601 --> 35:04.519
[sighs]

35:05.895 --> 35:07.730
But the world is changing.

35:10.399 --> 35:11.317
[sighs]

35:12.026 --> 35:14.195
So I guess
I'm gonna have to change with it.

35:17.532 --> 35:19.367
You gotta do what you gotta do.

35:22.120 --> 35:23.329
[Hutch] Oh, Linus?

35:26.666 --> 35:28.626
I'm gonna need one more thing from you.

35:29.877 --> 35:32.672
Consider it a… an advance.

35:41.180 --> 35:43.933
It's all there, plus ten percent.

35:45.726 --> 35:49.105
-You can count it.
-We are friends, yes?

35:49.605 --> 35:52.441
-[sighs]
-Who can we trust if not each other?

35:52.525 --> 35:53.359
[Hutch] Mm-hmm.

35:53.442 --> 35:55.361
-You got what I need?
-Of course.

36:00.408 --> 36:05.288
I don't need to remind you
to be extremely careful with this, yes?

36:06.372 --> 36:07.498
Will it work?

36:08.499 --> 36:11.752
I constructed it myself, so, yes,

36:13.129 --> 36:15.840
it will probably work.

36:15.923 --> 36:16.757
"Probably"?

36:17.758 --> 36:22.054
What is in this case
could power a small city for a year

36:22.847 --> 36:27.268
or punch a hole
through the mightiest being on the planet.

36:28.936 --> 36:31.397
Whatever strikes your fancy.

36:34.901 --> 36:36.569
I'll keep that in mind.

36:37.236 --> 36:38.154
[man] Hmm.

36:40.281 --> 36:42.575
[suspenseful music playing]

36:44.327 --> 36:46.037
["Painting the Clouds
With Sunshine" playing]

36:46.120 --> 36:48.456
♪ When I pretend I'm gay ♪

36:48.539 --> 36:51.167
♪ I never feel that way ♪

36:51.250 --> 36:53.794
♪ I'm only painting the clouds ♪

36:53.878 --> 36:55.963
♪ With sunshine ♪

36:56.047 --> 36:58.299
♪ When I hold back a tear ♪

36:58.382 --> 37:00.760
♪ To make a smile appear ♪

37:00.843 --> 37:03.679
♪ I'm only painting the clouds ♪

37:03.763 --> 37:05.389
♪ With sunshine ♪

37:06.098 --> 37:08.142
♪ Painting the blues beautiful hues ♪

37:08.226 --> 37:10.937
♪ Colored with gold and old rose ♪

37:11.020 --> 37:15.608
♪ Playing the clown
Trying to drown all of my woes ♪

37:15.691 --> 37:18.110
♪ Though things may not look bright ♪

37:18.194 --> 37:20.613
♪ They all turn out all right ♪

37:20.696 --> 37:23.407
♪ If I keep painting the clouds ♪

37:23.491 --> 37:25.910
♪ With sunshine ♪

37:30.331 --> 37:32.792
Good morning, sir. I trust you slept well?

37:32.875 --> 37:34.961
Oh, yes, fine. Thank you, Cuthbert.

37:36.963 --> 37:38.965
Has Wingate sent over the executed papers?

37:39.048 --> 37:39.924
Yes, sir.

37:40.007 --> 37:43.511
He has graciously agreed
to allow adequate time

37:43.594 --> 37:45.888
for you to secure
other living arrangements.

37:45.972 --> 37:46.806
And the staff?

37:46.889 --> 37:49.934
Well, they have been
adequately compensated, sir,

37:50.017 --> 37:51.477
thanks to your generosity.

37:51.560 --> 37:52.979
Hmm. Good, good.

37:54.522 --> 37:55.773
How'd they take it?

37:55.856 --> 37:57.608
[Cuthbert]
As well as can be expected, sir.

37:57.692 --> 37:58.526
[George] Hmm.

38:00.653 --> 38:06.617
I took the liberty of averaging
all of your selections over the last year

38:07.326 --> 38:08.869
and arrived at the estimation

38:08.953 --> 38:12.707
number 58 will be most appropriate
this morning, sir.

38:12.790 --> 38:13.708
[clears throat]

38:14.583 --> 38:16.002
Thank you, Cuthbert. I…

38:18.379 --> 38:19.380
[exhales]

38:21.882 --> 38:23.384
[whispers] Thank you. [sniffles]

38:27.221 --> 38:28.597
Of… of course, sir.

38:29.473 --> 38:30.433
[sighs]

38:32.101 --> 38:35.771
There are still details to be attended to…

38:37.857 --> 38:40.860
if you don't require anything else, sir.

38:42.945 --> 38:44.363
That'll be all. Thank you.

38:46.907 --> 38:47.825
[inhales sharply]

38:55.082 --> 38:56.000
[sniffles]

39:22.360 --> 39:24.612
[suspenseful music playing]

40:08.114 --> 40:09.698
-[zaps]
-[gasps]

40:16.622 --> 40:17.998
[Hutch] Almost there, Pops.

40:21.001 --> 40:22.128
Almost there.

40:22.211 --> 40:23.712
[welder sizzling]

40:24.422 --> 40:27.466
["Painting the Clouds
With Sunshine" playing]

40:27.550 --> 40:29.969
♪ Though things may not look bright ♪

40:30.052 --> 40:32.430
♪ They all turn out all right ♪

40:32.513 --> 40:35.266
♪ If I keep painting the clouds ♪

40:35.349 --> 40:37.643
♪ With sunshine ♪

40:40.980 --> 40:43.899
[ominous music playing]
